article.headline: CS Bakersfield 80, Sacramento St. 78
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. -- Alex Johnson nailed a 3-pointer with 20 seconds left in overtime to give Cal State Bakersfield an 80-78 victory over Sacramento State on Sunday night. The Hornets (0-1) trailed only once in regulation and led by as many as 10 in the second half, but Bakersfield (1-1) chipped away until Johnson sent the game to overtime tied at 73 by converting three free throws with three seconds left. He then banged in a 3-pointer to give the Roadrunners a 79-77 edge with 20 seconds left in overtime. After a free throw, the Roadrunners led 80-77. Then the Hornets' Antoine Proctor sank a free throw and missed the second. He got the rebound, but his attempted game-winner was off the mark. Johnson led all scorers with 22, and Stephon Carter had 19. Alpha N'Diaye led Sacramento State with 16. John Dickson added 15 and Sultan Toles-Bey and Proctor 14 apiece.
